pr_body:
Changelog:

@andrewkress  - only save token to disk if reuse session is true #81
@tchellomello - Getting TypeError #86

To avoid corruption of zip files when running the WebUI on Windows. This does not affect Linux.

See https://docs.python.org/2/library/functions.html#open
@ptormene had a similar issues with the QGIS plugin...

if running from zsh the activate script without the quote, you will get an error of the following:

Scripts/activate:40: = not found

This is only affecting when running from cygwin.
